I understand what your concern is, but I don't quite understand your approach, sorry if I didn't get this right.

I added a test that adds a `BottomAppBarTheme` with 0 params, then I check that the child `BottomAppBar` defaults are right.

```
  testWidgets('BAB theme does not affect defaults', (WidgetTester tester) async {
    await tester.pumpWidget(MaterialApp(
      theme: ThemeData(bottomAppBarTheme: const BottomAppBarTheme()),
      home: const Scaffold(body: BottomAppBar()),
    ));

    final PhysicalShape widget = _getBabRenderObject(tester);

    expect(widget.color, Colors.white);
    expect(widget.elevation, equals(8.0));
  });
```

Is this what you were looking for?

No it isn't.  The idea is to verify that all of the BAB properties have the same values as they had before this PR, even though those values are now retrieved "through" the theme.
```
await tester.pumpWidget(
  MaterialApp(home: const Scaffold(body: BottomAppBar())),
);
// Now verify that all of the BAB properties have the same values as they would if 
// you ran this test against Flutter 1.0
```

